{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:09:40.367043+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is the full inventory registered in `gita/cmds.json` on the `master` branch of `rpnr-bench/T09_R02`.\n\n---\n\n### Subcommands and their underlying `git` commands\n\n| Subcommand | Git command executed | Help text |\n|------------|----------------------|-----------|\n| `br` | `git branch -vv` | show local branches |\n| `clean` | `git clean -dfx` | remove all untracked files/folders |\n| `diff` | `git diff` | git show differences |\n| `difftool` | `git difftool` | show differences using a tool |\n| `fetch` | `git fetch` | fetch remote update |\n| `last` | `git log -1 HEAD` | show log information of HEAD |\n| `lo` | `git log --oneline -7` | show one-line log for the latest 7 commits |\n| `log` | `git log` | show logs |\n| `merge` | `git merge @{u}` | merge remote updates |\n| `mergetool` | `git mergetool` | merge updates with a tool |\n| `patch` | `git format-patch HEAD~` | make a patch |\n| `pull` | `git pull` | pull remote updates |\n| `push` | `git push` | push the local updates |\n| `rebase` | `git rebase` | rebase from master |\n| `reflog` | `git reflog` | show ref logs |\n| `remote` | `git remote -v` | show remote settings |\n| `reset` | `git reset` | reset repo(s) |\n| `show` | `git show` | show detailed commit information |\n| `stash` | `git stash` | store uncommited changes |\n| `stat` | `git diff --stat` | show edit statistics |\n| `st` | `git status` | show status |\n| `tag` | `git tag -n` | show tags |\n\n---\n\n### Entries with `allow_all`\n\nThese subcommands accept arbitrary extra arguments from the command line (the `allow_all` flag permits passing through additional user-supplied flags):\n\n- **`fetch`**\n- **`lo`**\n- **`pull`**\n- **`push`**\n- **`stat`**\n- **`st`**\n\n### Entries with `disable_async`\n\nThese subcommands force synchronous execution (they opt out of the default asynchronous runner):\n\n- **`difftool`**\n- **`log`**\